I am comparing #LaCasaDePapel  to 3 sagas I like first one is #GoT another TV series with many seasons except #GoT had a multidimensional story with a lot of dynamic subplots going on. It had to much to tell that even 8 seasons was very small and not enough to tell it

So after watching season 4 of #LaCasaDePapel my conclusion is the same about it. It is not bad or even worse than the previous seasons. The problem is simply that they have no story to tell. Their plot has nothing to offer and it is extremely flat. I mean there is no progress.

What make people angry now is that #LaCasaDePapel had sold itself as a clever challenging show. I mean one doesn't watch it to see explosions and action sequences but to outwit himself and that doesn't happen anymore. Now it's just a clever cash grab not cheap but still cash grab

#GoT with each season added new plots, characters and arcs and had literally a full world to go on. In contrast #LaCasaDePapel has only bank, tent, and operation room. This limits the possibilities of building new arcs or raising the plot layers to have multidimensional motive

first hints of the horcruxes, book 3 who the traitor is, etc.) In contrast there is nothingnof these aspects in #LaCasaDePapel both stories are similar and only more developed conflicts raise but nothing else happens. We steal a bank, the crew has some tension, but nothing more
